      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are looking kind of sickly. the leaves on the bottom are turning yellow and falling off. what do you think is going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your tomato plants might be experiencing a case of root rot, which is a common issue that can cause the leaves to yellow and fall off. This can be caused by overwatering or poor drainage. Consider checking the soil moisture and drainage, and ensure the plants are not sitting in water. You might also want to look for any signs of pests or diseases. \n\nSpeaking of pests, have you noticed any tiny, green, and striped insects on your plants? They could be aphids, which are another common problem. If that's the case, you might need to introduce some natural predators like ladybugs, or use an insecticidal soap to get rid of them. \n\nIn the meantime, make sure to keep an eye on your tomato plants and take action as soon as you notice any signs of trouble. Good luck!",
